NB - Grizzly has moved to Eclipse Foundation! 
https://github.com/eclipse-ee4j/grizzly.git

GrizzlyHttpServerFactory + Jersey + Bean Validation 
(jersey-container-grizzly2-servlet/jersey-bean-validation ver 2.12, 
grizzly-http-server ver 2.3.16, hibernate-validator ver 5.0.0.Final)

The 400 errors generated by a ValidationException are returning Grizzly's 
default error page (html) instead of the Bean Validation's Response 
entity (json). I've tried a ClientResponseFilter and its entityStream 
also contains the html error page.

When I run the system under Tomcat, the ValidationExceptions return a Response with a json-formatted entity.
